A well known Private Equity business with over  billion assets under management, with offices based in Sydney, Tokyo, London and Chicago.

Role
Working very closely with the investment and investor relations team;
Conduct analysis of potential acquisition opportunities and preparation of valuation models used for pricing acquisition bids;
Participate in due diligence processes and project management of the acquisition processes – maintenance and ongoing update of acquisition valuation models, analysis of data room information and key assumptions and provide other analytic solutions to transaction requirements, including sensitivity and scenario analysis, synergies analysis, and deal structuring – (Please see below for selected list of transactions);
Management of semiannual internal asset valuation process required for financial reporting, and prepare internal profit and loss, cash flow and balance sheet forecasts for group CFO;
Preparation of company semi-annual investor reports and presentations.
Compensation

Up to k, plus super, plus a bonus.

 -  a yearMandarin skills advantageous

Suited for Entry-Level candidates
Oriental Merchant is an established importer and distributor of authentic Asian groceries, working with many brands that are familiar throughout the Asia Pacific region.
As an IT Analyst Programmer/Developer, you will play an important role in the continuous enhancement and operational support of current software applications (SAP, Warehouse Management, and Sales Software), as well as assist the Senior team member for the design, coding and implementation of IT projects and product development.
A fantastic opportunity for applicants who are excited about IT and want to take their programming career to the next level.
You will be responsible for but not limited to the following:
Carrying our support phone calls on a rotating basis, occasionally at odd-hours;
Provide support on databases, applications, servers and network systems;
Communicating with business to identify, analyse, define, and document requirements for workflow, processes and system interfaces;
Ability to design, develop and test computer applications to meet business requirements in timely manner;
Maintaining IT’s support for the various divisions and assisting with the development of software solutions for business units;
Developing and maintaining IT’s monitoring tools, dashboard, Policy/Knowledge-base and intranet page;
Delivering 1st and 2nd level hardware support to internal users and customers;
Manage backups and disaster recovery systems of all data, storage and network systems;
Provide ad-hoc training and advice to end-users in the efficient use of company’s IT software, hardware and applications as required.
We regret that only short-listed candidates will be contacted.
Requirements
Essential Skills and Experience We Are Looking For:
Degree in computer science or technical discipline;
Experience in programming and System administrative would be highly regarded;
Advanced Excel UI skills, writing macros (in Visual Basic for Applications) and handling databases (MS SQL Server);
Programming skills in VBA, C#, Objective C, JAVA and PHP;
Advanced knowledge of IT concepts and frameworks;
Experienced in O365, Mobile Apps, Active directory, PowerShell, VMware and NAS storage would be an advantage;
Strong and diligent with technical based documentation;
Ability to think laterally with good analytical and problem-solving skills;
Must have excellent written and verbal English language competency to liaise within the business and clients;
Chinese language skills are not necessary but advantageous due to partnership engagement of Chinese counterpart.
The IT Analyst Programmer/Developer will be based in Mulgrave, but candidate must be comfortable with occasionally travelling between our office locations.

 a yearOur client is a leading Funds Management business and currently requires an Investment Operations Analyst.

Your role is to help with managing investment funds and mandates.

In this exciting and diverse role you will be responsible for:
Trade settlements and corporate actions across various Funds and Investment Mandates;
Reconciliation of data, holdings and bank details;
Managing instructions to custodians; and
Contribute towards improvement and development of investment processes and performance.
Working in a driven and dynamic team environment, you gain exposure to multiple facets of the business and funds operations. You will be a dependable team player, a self-starter with a natural passion for financial markets and managed funds. The ideal candidate will have previous investment operations experience from a funds management or custody background and will have the ability to work independently in a time critical and high-performing environment.

Technical Skills & Qualifications required include:
Finance/Business degree qualified and post-graduate qualifications highly regarded;
Minimum 2 years’ experience in investment operations (corporate actions, reconciliations, trade executions and settlements experience a must);
An understanding of Australian and global investment markets/instruments, regulations and governance requirements;
Proven stakeholder management and problem-solving abilities; and
Strong Excel/Word skills and very strong attention to detail.
This is an exciting opportunity at a market leading funds management business which is forecasting significant growth and provides the best training in the market.

If you are interested in learning more about this position, please contact Nupur Gill at Kaizen Recruitment on 03 9111 0128 or apply via the attached email link.

