Brisbane QLDContract -  an hourBrisbane CBD
Multiple roles
Great outcomes for QLD’ers
Leading state government department has multiple requirements for highly skilled and experienced Senior Business Analysts to join them on initial contracts through until June 30 with highly likely extensions. You will be working with a diverse range of stakeholders and delivering great outcomes for the wider community.

Key Responsibilities – Duties – Skills Set

Identify, evaluate, prioritise and recommend options to resolve business problems or capitalise on business opportunities that may include process improvement, systems enhancement, user training, software changes, and/or integration opportunities;
Undertake information gathering and analysis, providing information to assist with organisational performance improvements and to capture and disseminate technical and business information;
Facilitate open communication and discussion between stakeholders, using feedback to assess and promote understanding of need for future changes in services, products and systems;
Effectively liaise with business and technical stakeholders to identify and validate ICT business requirements;
Resolve conflicting requirements and work with the business representatives to determine priorities and validate and justify the requirements against the project business outcomes;
Provide timely, strategic and expert advice to the project manager and business representatives regarding system requirements, information requirements, business impacts, scope management and project risks; and
Coordinate business analysis work with Organisational change management activities to ensure the business are supported through the change process and the business changes align with departmental policies and procedures.
Essential

Minimum six years’ experience as a Business Analyst in a project or program environment within Government;
Knowledge and experience in business transformation preferably using Lean methodologies and best practices;
Knowledge and experience in both waterfall and Agile project and program delivery and Agile requirements analysis and definition (e.g. MoSCoW analysis method, timeboxing);
Proven track record to quickly understand the key value drivers of a business, how they impact the scope and approach of program / project definition;
Possess commercial acumen with ability to tailor solutions to enhance effectiveness and to identify valuable client development opportunities;
Highly developed interpersonal skills particularly in conceptualisation and communication of reporting, analysis, collection and technical matters to a range of audiences;
Excellent written skills, with a focus on clear presentation in plain English;
Experience in developing project documentation and/or technical specifications; and
Experience within the development of business process mapping, current and future states using Business Process Model and Notation (BPMN).
Deliverables

Prioritisation of ICT enabled initiatives and high level options analysis to inform Program scope and Project start-ups;
Once prioritised, detailed requirements and options analysis to inform Project Approaches;
Business Requirements Specification including current and future state processes;
Register of process and policy changes required to support the business;
Other project artefacts as required; and
Facilitation of workshops to elicit requirements and support business process improvement.
For more information please call Ben Pace at u&u on 07 3232 9112, quoting reference number 14026. Alternatively, to submit an application, please click below.

Please submit your resume in Word format only.

 -  a dayContractNewly created role
High profile portfolio
Multiple roles
Primary Role Purpose

The primary purpose of the role is to:

Establish and document a full set of prioritised, business-approved UAT scenarios and test cases, to be utilised within the User Acceptance Test phase of the EAMS program; and
Manage time and workload efficiently, working with multiple, extremely busy, resources to establish full test coverage, it is imperative to maximise time spent with resources to achieve this end goal.
Role Accountabilities

The QUU Senior Test Analyst has the following accountabilities:

Will form part of a small team who will document the full scope of UAT, along with any test data or pre-requisite test condition necessary to execute all of the test cases;
Execute these test cases (pre-UAT) to identify and eradicate as many Critical or High severity defects prior to formal UAT commencing;
Provide test support to business resources as they execute their UAT test cases from within a cloud-based instance of HP ALM;
Ensure that all deviations from Expected Outcomes are duly captured within HP ALM and seen through to resolution;
Supporting the Test Manager in any subsequent triage and re-test process as required; and
Showcase end solution as required to the QUU business resources within the testing window.
Knowledge and Experience

The role requires the following knowledge and experience:

Proven experience, working both individually as well as part of a team, across a number of major ERP projects, ideally EAMS-related, establishing a business-approved, prioritised suite of test scenarios and test cases, ideally in these modules:
Asset & Work Management;
Finance & Human Resources;
Procurement & Supply Chain;
Clear understanding of project process, life-cycle and relationship between phases, quality management and scope;
Ability to work closely with business representatives, stream leads and project team members, often on highly sensitive and confidential matter;
Proven experience working with both offshore and/or external vendors and/or service providers in order to deliver a successful project outcome; and
Demonstrated test experience within differing types of System Delivery Life Cycles, e.g. Waterfall, Iterative, Agile etc.
For more information please call Ben Pace or Nicky Stanway at u&u, quoting reference number 14164. Alternatively, to submit an application, please click below.

Please submit your resume in Word format only.

